data.description: Perfect piece of paradise! Incredible, cutom-built log home on over six acres, with a two-acre private pond! Paddle boat and electric boat are included, and the pond is stocked with spawning trout (rainbow, cutthroat, and golden). This home has a rich history, including the logs of the home harvested from the Yellowstone wildfire. You'll in love with the 3-story river stone fire column, running through the middle of the home from the basement to the ceiling. Large windows provide beautiful natural light and scenic views. Keep an eye out for moose, deer, elk, eagles, and even wild turkeys. Practice your bow hunting on the indoor Olympic-length archery range in the basement! Winters will be comfy and cozy with the circulating hot water system and fireplaces in the basement and on the main floor. There is ample storage space, and a built-in safe! This property is truly one-of-a-kind!
